      <title>Impressions of a Vah Shir coming home.</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Roleplaying&amp;message.id=12469#M12469</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;In a lonely night of December I came home&lt;br&gt;I saw the walls of Shar Vahl carry the sky&lt;br&gt;My heart leaped in joy, once again filled with hope&lt;br&gt;Great was my confusion as I saw I was alone&lt;br&gt;No one on the streets but old citizens, no young Khati Sha&lt;br&gt;Or Taruun, no young Vah shir at all.&lt;br&gt;My heart cried. Our glorious city was left&lt;br&gt;And I felt my whole life was in vain.&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;But I ventured on, through the Shadeweavers Thicket&lt;br&gt;And down to the Caverns. I killed the fiends that dwell&lt;br&gt;There under the surface, I swam in moldy waters,&lt;br&gt;I walked through the streets of the Shadowhaven&lt;br&gt;And I reached Nexus... I saw that everything changed.&lt;br&gt;What happened to our nation, to our children, to our hopes&lt;br&gt;Was everything wasted, am I cursed to travel alone?&lt;br&gt;But still I feel there is no better place than my home.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Sat, 09 Dec 2006 16:30:50 GMT</pubDate>
      <author>Shadowteeth</author>
      <guid>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Roleplaying&amp;message.id=12469#M12469</guid>
