    <item>
      <title>Farewell OWD Bash  Part 1 -------  Lady Vox</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Roleplaying&amp;message.id=12468#M12468</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;OWD is a group of raiders who have been raiding Lord Nagafen and Lady Vox on the Tunare Server for a long time but is not reaching the end of its run since I am the last Raid Leader for the group.&amp;nbsp; In tribute to OWD and in Thanks for them helping people get epic drops from these two dragons, my warrior, Shinu Swiftpaw, decided to pull off two final raids on these two dragons and slap them around with his shiny new epic swords.&amp;nbsp; Below is a fictional account of the first of these last two raids which was on Lady Vox on 10-29-06.&amp;nbsp; The actual raid took us about 6 hrs and had 1 wipe.&amp;nbsp; (Lady Vox was so glad to see us that she kept coming out of her lair to greet us.)&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Old World Dragons:&amp;nbsp; Vox&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The Vah Shir quickly ran across the snowy landscape of Everfrost Peaks heading to the meeting place in Permafrost Keep.&amp;nbsp; This warrior's reputation had grown so much that even the Orcs that were patrolling hid in fear of him.&amp;nbsp; As he approached the entrance to the keep he slowed a little looking for signs of any of the Ice Giant guards.&amp;nbsp; Two of them were sleeping in the guard houses just inside the gate.&amp;nbsp; So the warrior slipped into the compound and into the keep where he found one that was awake and had apparently never heard the name of Shinu Swiftpaw.&amp;nbsp; Shinu was a White Tiger Clan Vah Shir who had grown up in Shar Vahl and then journeyed to Norrath to seek adventure and food.&amp;nbsp; The fight did not take long and Shinu had the Giant dead on the icy floor.&amp;nbsp; Shinu picked up what trinkets the Giant had on him to sell to the vendors in New Tanaan.&amp;nbsp; Shinu had a few minor cuts on him from the fight so he sat for a minute and willed them closed in the manner that Master Benniwan had taught him.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Master Benniwan was a Grandmaster monk of Quellious in Freeport who trained the Elite of the monks known as the White Lotus Clan.&amp;nbsp; It was there that Shinu met Soonguyen Ironfist who got Master Benniwan to take Shinu in for some training.&amp;nbsp; Master Benniwan's wife, Extacee was probably the most beautiful Vah Shir swordmaiden Shinu had ever seen.&amp;nbsp; Shinu thought it strange that one of his kind would join with a Furless but, then Shinu had seen quite a few strange things in his career.&amp;nbsp; Master Benniwan taught Shinu several mental techniques that would allow him to resist magical attacks better and also to help him heal a little faster for short periods of time.&amp;nbsp; Master Benniwan also showed him a few new tricks to add to his swordsmanship repertoire.&amp;nbsp; Shinu trained there until Soonguyen graduated and then the two of them took off for adventure.&amp;nbsp; Shinu had fought as a mercenary in several campaigns including the battle for the Firiona Vie outpost and the relocating of the Frogloks of Gukta to Rathe Mountains.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Just before Shinu joined the Frogloks in their fight, he had started gathering stories and information about two imprisoned Dragons in Lavastorm Mountains and in Permafrost Keep, Lord Nagafen and Lady Vox.&amp;nbsp; These two were imprisoned because of their desire to join their souls, which would have brought about another dragon like Kerafyrm.&amp;nbsp; Shinu heard tales of great treasures being held in their lairs and also that killing them would not invoke the wrath of any of the other Dragons of Norrath.&amp;nbsp; So Shinu sent spies into both lairs to find the locations of the Dragons' lairs and to see if he could form a strategy to take these two great Dragons down.&amp;nbsp; Shinu started gathering friends to him who were of like mind to take these two out and eventually called their band of mercenaries Old World Dragons.&amp;nbsp; After the battles in the Mountains of Rathe had ceased and the Frogloks had their home, Shinu returned to his home in Shar Vahl where he waited as reports from his spies came in.&amp;nbsp; Eventually Shinu had maps of both lairs and a listing of what creatures were there, their strengths, weaknesses and locations.&amp;nbsp; Shinu called together his band of adventurers and developed a plan for each lair and what it would take to pull each off.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Today they were to put their plan to the test on Lady Vox.&amp;nbsp; There would be only one attempt on this creature for to fail would be the death of the whole group.&amp;nbsp; Shinu had made several trips into the Keep and had retrieved items from there that he needed in order to secure his new swords.&amp;nbsp; That quest is another story.&amp;nbsp; As Shinu ran to the Goblin King's main hall most of the goblins he encountered fled in fear from him and his glowing swords.&amp;nbsp; A couple of the Goblins decided to try him but Shinu did not stop until he entered the main hall.&amp;nbsp; Once in the main hall, Shinu quickly slew the king and the High Priest and then started on the guards.&amp;nbsp; The Goblins that tried to engage him on his way in arrived shortly afterward but non were any match for the Blue-clad warrior.&amp;nbsp; Shinu had the main hall cleared in a matter of minutes.&amp;nbsp; All the fighting made him hungry so he started a fire and carved out a few steaks from the dead Goblins to cook on it.&amp;nbsp; As Shinu finished the last steak, Soonguyen arrived followed shortly afterward by the rest of the Old World Dragons.&amp;nbsp; The group could hear the echoing of the Ice Giant guardians’ footsteps as they wandered around in Lady Vox’s lair.&amp;nbsp; Once everyone was assembled, Shinu addressed the adventurers.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;“You all know the plan.&amp;nbsp; We only get one shot at this.&amp;nbsp; If we fail there will be no survivors, except maybe Soonguyen, to tell the tale.&amp;nbsp; Katayana, please assemble your team and prepare to begin.&amp;nbsp; Everyone else find a hiding place.”&amp;nbsp; Katayana traced the runes on her bracelet and an eye appeared floating in the air.&amp;nbsp; Katayana moved the eye through the hallways passed the giants, who gave it no notice and into Lady Vox’s lair.&amp;nbsp; Katayana played a low tune on her flute and bound her sight to Lady Vox so she could see what the Dragon Saw.&amp;nbsp; Soonguyen went to the door leading to the hall and opened it.&amp;nbsp; The Ice Giant on the other side saw the small Human and immediately attacked.&amp;nbsp; Soonguyen dodged the Giant’s blow and ran back into the main hall and played dead.&amp;nbsp; The giant came around the corner and saw Soonguyen lying on the ground and moved closer to investigate.&amp;nbsp; Thagar and Shinu jumped out of their hiding places and attacked the giant.&amp;nbsp; The rest of the band joined in right after.&amp;nbsp; Within a few seconds the Giant was overwhelmed and dead.&amp;nbsp; The group quickly removed the body and Soonguyen went back into the halls to get more Giants and eventually the giant spider that was in there too.&amp;nbsp; Several times during the course of this routine Lady Vox and her guardians came out to investigate but found the main hall to be empty as everyone had gone back to their hiding places and had the bodies of the giants hidden away.&amp;nbsp; Eventually it came down to Lady Vox and her guardian Giants left inside her lair.&amp;nbsp; Soonguyen and Tortuur went to the door of her lair where Tortuur cast his Feign Death spell and appeared dead on the ground blocking the door to Lady Vox’s lair open.&amp;nbsp; Soonguyen slipped inside and threw a dart at the Icy Terror he found not too far inside.&amp;nbsp; The Terror then gave chase to Soonguyen who ran from the lair.&amp;nbsp; The Giants and Lady Vox seeing the Icy Terror leave the lair followed behind it.&amp;nbsp; They all ignored the seemingly dead necromancer at the doorway thinking that another of their number had slain it.&amp;nbsp; The giants followed the Icy Terror around the corner where they found it poking a human that appeared dead as well.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;“All of you stay out here and keep watch.”&amp;nbsp; Said Lady Vox.&amp;nbsp; “I am going to take a nap and dream of that hot red Dragon Lord Nagafen.”&amp;nbsp; Lady Vox then walked back into her lair and laid down for a nap.&amp;nbsp; Tortuur Immediately stood up and ran back to the adventurers in the main hall making sure that the Giants and the Icy Terror saw him.&amp;nbsp; All of the Giants and the Icy terror followed Tortuur to the main hall where Tortuur cast his feign death spell again.&amp;nbsp; Thagar and Shinu again jumped out and engaged the group that had been brought to them.&amp;nbsp; The rest of the Old World Dragons group quickly joined in the fight which lasted several minutes.&amp;nbsp; The Giants and the Icy Terror were now all dead and nothing left between the adventurers and Lady Vox.&amp;nbsp; The group moved close to Lady Vox’s lair and could hear her snoring inside.&amp;nbsp; Shinu gave final instructions to the group and walked up to the lair door.&amp;nbsp; Shinu stepped inside the lair and looked at the sleeping dragon for a minute before he sharpened his claws on the wall, leaving deep gouges in the once smooth surface.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;“Here Leezard, Leezard!”&amp;nbsp; Shouted Shinu as he charged the Ice Queen.&amp;nbsp; Lady Vox upon hearing the taunt immediately woke up and turned toward the blue armored White Tiger Clan Vah Shir that was charging toward her with his glowing blades swinging.&amp;nbsp; Lady Vox blew an icy breath at Shinu who, thanks to some magical protections and the training he received from Master Benniwan, was able to withstand it with little harm to himself.&amp;nbsp; Shinu cut two quick gashes into Lady Vox’s scaly skin and called out for his friends to assist.&amp;nbsp; The rest of the band entered the lair and charged the Dragon.&amp;nbsp; The Tortuur sent his after the Dragon along with the others who had pets.&amp;nbsp; Katayana stood under Lady Vox and played her magical tunes that helped her friends resist Lady Vox’s magical attacks.&amp;nbsp; Haroel, Branlaven and Linsang kept their healing prayers going for the rest of the attackers.&amp;nbsp; Enamlat, Shinu, Thagar, Baeba, Waofno and Endered kept their swords slicing into the Dragon’s flesh.&amp;nbsp; Skwishy stood next to Katayana and kept casting her spells to damage the Dragon more.&amp;nbsp; After what seemed like an hour of constant fighting Lady Vox fell over dead.&amp;nbsp; The group was exhausted but still managed to yell out a shout of cheer.&amp;nbsp; The group divided up what treasures they found in the lair and Shinu cut up quite a few steaks from the carcass of the once great Ice Dragon.&amp;nbsp; “Great work all of you.&amp;nbsp; Let us go rest for a week and we will gather in Lavastorm Mountains at the Druid rings for our attack on Lord Nagafen afterward.&amp;nbsp; After he is done I think we will all be set for life.”&amp;nbsp; The Old World Dragons walked out of Permafrost keep and returned to their homes.&amp;nbsp; &lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
      <pubDate>Mon, 30 Oct 2006 22:53:35 GMT</pubDate>
      <author>Gilliadson</author>
