    <item>
      <title>The New Shadowbane Part 1</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Roleplaying&amp;message.id=12466#M12466</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;Chapter 1:&amp;nbsp; Homecoming&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Father, the fate of Norrath is tied to the fate of Veeshan's children.&amp;nbsp; Even you should realize this."&amp;nbsp; Said the younger knight.&amp;nbsp; "Consult with Willa in this matter.&amp;nbsp; For the last four generations, excepting a good portion of your life, she has been a valuable source of wisdom for our family.&amp;nbsp; She even knows this to be true.&amp;nbsp; Did you not think that I would consult her before broaching this subject with you?"&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Son,” Said the elder Shadowbane, "for generations, not only have we Knights of Truth been the guardians of all that is good in Freeport but we have also been on the front line to help keep Veeshan's children in check.&amp;nbsp; Now you come to me saying you wish to enter the Holy Union with one?&amp;nbsp; How did you expect me to react?"&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Father, she is a child of Keikolin, one of the most noble of the Dragons that created the Drakkins.&amp;nbsp; Surely, you would know that I would choose a mate of such caliber.&amp;nbsp; You will have the opportunity to meet her soon.&amp;nbsp; She should be arriving today."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Lord Gilliadson," interjected Willa, "think on this.&amp;nbsp; The Dragon Nest is no more.&amp;nbsp; When the last of the great Dragons passes from this world then Norrath will be no more unless this new breed carries the blood of Veeshan onward.&amp;nbsp; When Veeshan laid her claim to this world, she tied its fate to that of her children.&amp;nbsp; As long as her bloodline lives in this world, then this world will continue.&amp;nbsp; It is really a wise thing that Shadowbanes should have a hand in keeping Norrath.&amp;nbsp; In this way also, your family will still serve to keep Veeshan's children in check by aligning with the most noble of the line."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Your wisdom is sound and irrefutable as usual, Willa.&amp;nbsp; However, we will discuss this further at the Homecoming.&amp;nbsp; In the meantime, I would like you to fetch Zephistophiles from his tavern.&amp;nbsp; I would very much like to hear his opinion as well when we have this discussion."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"A wise choice Lord Gilliadson.&amp;nbsp; Zephistophiles is about as well versed in lore as I am.&amp;nbsp; Master Darthan, if you would be so kind as to fetch our bard friend after your chosen arrives, I will prepare a room for him.&amp;nbsp; Your mother should be returning within the next few days.&amp;nbsp; With your permission, Lord Gilliadson, I shall also prepare a room for your son's chosen.&amp;nbsp; I can sense her presence in the Commonlands and she is coming to us now.&amp;nbsp; I know your feelings but I would respectfully suggest diplomacy until you get to know her."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Unless she proves dishonorable, she is to be accorded the same respect as Lady Obsecion and Lutiana.&amp;nbsp; I will treat her as an honored guest.&amp;nbsp; My son is not known to be deficient in judgment.&amp;nbsp; When she arrives, bring her before me."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"So it shall be done."&amp;nbsp; Said Willa.&amp;nbsp; "I shall inform the staff."&amp;nbsp; Willa was about to leave when Gilliadson stopped her.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Tell me, Willa, what do you feel?"&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"I think your son has made a very wise choice in this.&amp;nbsp; I can feel no malice in her from here.&amp;nbsp; The future of Norrath hangs in the balance with this new race.&amp;nbsp; There are benevolent Drakkin as well as some not so well intentioned but they all work together toward the same goal of preserving the Wurm Queen's bloodline and the continuation of our world.&amp;nbsp; Both are honorable goals."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Thank you Willa."&amp;nbsp; The Halfling druid left the study to take care of the business at hand.&amp;nbsp; Darthan met the young Drakkin at the gate with an embrace and a kiss.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"My beloved!"&amp;nbsp; Exclaimed Darthan.&amp;nbsp; "I am so pleased to see you.&amp;nbsp; Please come in.&amp;nbsp; My father is waiting to meet you."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Vasha my love."&amp;nbsp; Said the Drakkin lady.&amp;nbsp; "I have missed being in your arms.&amp;nbsp; Please allow me to freshen up before appearing before your father."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Very well my dear."&amp;nbsp; The two of them walked into the manor and Darthan called one of the maids.&amp;nbsp; "Ninae, please take M'lady to freshen up and then to Willa.&amp;nbsp; Willa will bring her to the study."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"As you wish M'lord."&amp;nbsp; Ninae bowed.&amp;nbsp; "This way M'lady."&amp;nbsp; The young servant led the Drakkin to a washroom.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"My brother!"&amp;nbsp; Cried out a young lady knight as she ran up to Darthan, threw her arms around his neck and kissed him on the cheek.&amp;nbsp; "Is it true?&amp;nbsp; Have you really found a mate and have returned for Father's blessing?&amp;nbsp; Is she really a Drakkin?&amp;nbsp; When do I get to meet her?"&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Slow down Lutiana!&amp;nbsp; Yes to all and as soon as we are done meeting with Father."&amp;nbsp; Darthan held his sister in his arms for a moment and kissed her on her cheek.&amp;nbsp; "Is Mirthan returning home as well?"&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"We have not heard from him in quite some time.&amp;nbsp; He is off with Shinu's son the last we heard."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"I wonder how that cat is doing.&amp;nbsp; I have not seen him since he was a kit.&amp;nbsp; If he is anything like his father, then he is probably deep into something."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Probably so but Mirthan has never missed our annual gathering so if he is alive, he will be here."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"Very true.&amp;nbsp; I need to return to Father and present my lady to him.&amp;nbsp; I sincerely hope he approves."&amp;nbsp; Darthan went to the hall outside the study and waited for Willa and his companion.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"You have chosen a fine lady, Master Darthan."&amp;nbsp; Said Willa when the two of them arrived.&amp;nbsp; "Would you like me to accompany you both in?"&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"No Willa, we must do this on our own."&amp;nbsp; Darthan turned to his lady.&amp;nbsp; "Getting him to accept you is the easy part.&amp;nbsp; Father has always been a good judge of character.&amp;nbsp; Getting his blessing upon our Union is another matter.&amp;nbsp; If I were not his eldest son, I believe it would be a different matter."&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;"We will get passed this my love.&amp;nbsp; I know how important it is for you to have your father's blessing and I respect that.&amp;nbsp; We will also need to get the blessing of my progenitor as well but that should not be a difficult.”&amp;nbsp; The two of them entered the study and stood before Darthan’s father.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Father, I would like to present to you my chosen, Vallea, Daughter of Keikolin.”&amp;nbsp; Vallea bowed before the great knight and lord of the manor.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Welcome to my home Daughter of Keikolin.&amp;nbsp; Please, both of you take seats.”&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson yelled toward the door.&amp;nbsp; “Willa I know you are out there.&amp;nbsp; Would you bring us some to drinks?”&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson turned back toward the couple.&amp;nbsp; “Lady Vallea my son has told me much about you.&amp;nbsp; I have decided to give you the benefit of the doubt.&amp;nbsp; However, giving my blessing upon this Union is still a matter up for debate which will be decided at Homecoming.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“After what Darthan has told me about you I expected nothing less.&amp;nbsp; I will say that I love your son dearly and I honor your traditions.&amp;nbsp; Being a knight myself, I would be willing to go through whatever trials I must go through to prove myself worthy to you.”&amp;nbsp; Willa entered the room with drinks for all.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Thank you Willa.”&amp;nbsp; Said Gilliadson dismissing her form the room.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson then addressed his son.&amp;nbsp; “Your mother will have a say in this matter as well.&amp;nbsp; She should be back from Felwithe tomorrow.&amp;nbsp; I also received a dispatch from your brother but I haven’t told your sister yet.&amp;nbsp; He and Ralnu will be here in time for Homecoming.&amp;nbsp; He wants it to be a surprise to Lutiana.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“As you wish, Father.”&amp;nbsp; Said Darthan.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Lady Vallea, I would very much like to have a conversation with you alone if you are of a mind to do so.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Lord Shadowbane, I would be most delighted and honored.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“You conduct yourself with much honor and grace.&amp;nbsp; That is a good thing.&amp;nbsp; Darthan, I believe you have an errand to run.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Yes Father.”&amp;nbsp; Darthan left the room and went to prepare for his trip to Tuneweaver’s Tavern.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“I will not keep you long.&amp;nbsp; I would not wish to keep you from seeing the man you love off on his journey.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“He is leaving already?”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“He is going to fetch an old friend of mine to join us for Homecoming.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Zephistophiles Tuneweaver.&amp;nbsp; Darthan has told me about him as well.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“I am curious about you.&amp;nbsp; Please tell me about yourself.&amp;nbsp; I know you were Human before your ‘awakening’ I would like to know about that part of your life.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Well the short version is that I was one of the Knights of Love before I was invited to join with my progenitor.&amp;nbsp; So, it seemed only natural for me to continue as a Paladin in the fight against the unholy.&amp;nbsp; I met Darthan as I was on my way to Crescent Reach.&amp;nbsp; Darthan was well received among my new people.&amp;nbsp; Many there are familiar with the name of Shadowbane and after Darthan pledged to help us by keeping the undead Ogres at bay, many of those who were of darker persuasions previously in life welcomed him with open arms.&amp;nbsp; I myself fought side by side with him the entire time and have fallen in love with him.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Being a Paladin does much toward your case.&amp;nbsp; But you must realize also that Darthan is my eldest son and also the heir to this estate that I had rebuilt.&amp;nbsp; This is going to take much prayer on my part.&amp;nbsp; Go now and see my son off.&amp;nbsp; We will talk more over the next few days and tomorrow you will meet the fairest lady in all the land.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Good day to you Lord Shadowbane.&amp;nbsp; I look forward to meeting the mother of my love.”&amp;nbsp; Vallea went out to Darthan as he was preparing to mount up and walked into his arms.&amp;nbsp; The couple held each other for a few minutes gazing into each other’s eyes.&amp;nbsp; “Return swiftly my love.”&amp;nbsp; Vallea kissed Darthan passionately before he mounted his horse and rode off to Qeynos Hills.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
