    <item>
      <title>The New Shadowbane Part 2</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Roleplaying&amp;message.id=12465#M12465</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Chapter 2:&amp;nbsp; Reunions&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Lady Obsecion returned early the next day and went to her husband first.&amp;nbsp; “I have sorely missed you Beloved.”&amp;nbsp; She said as she threw her arms around his neck.&amp;nbsp; “I wish you could have come with me on this journey but I know that making sure that preparations for Homecoming are completed on time is important.&amp;nbsp; How are the preparations coming along and which of our children have arrived so far?&amp;nbsp; I also have a surprise for you as well.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Well, my darling, the preparations are coming along nicely.”&amp;nbsp; Replied Gilliadson as he held his wife close.&amp;nbsp; “Willa has been most efficient.&amp;nbsp; Darthan and Lutiana are here and Mirthan is on his way.&amp;nbsp; He wants his coming to be a surprise to Lutiana.&amp;nbsp; Darthan also brought home a lady whom he intends to take as his wife.&amp;nbsp; You can meet with her at your leisure.&amp;nbsp; Now what is this surprise you have for me?”&amp;nbsp; Obsecion went to the door of their bedroom and opened it.&amp;nbsp; In walked two Koada`Dal arcanists.&amp;nbsp; “Sineliniel!&amp;nbsp; Elwinde!&amp;nbsp; By the sword of Marr it’s been a long time since I’ve seen you two!”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“It has been a long time indeed Cousin!”&amp;nbsp; Replied the twins in unison.&amp;nbsp; “There is one other here to see you.”&amp;nbsp; Another Koada`Dal lady entered the room.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Mother!&amp;nbsp; You have no idea how it pleases me to see you here as well!”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“This is the annual Shadowbane Homecoming is it not and the fifth such?&amp;nbsp; I would not have missed this one for anything.”&amp;nbsp; Said Lady Mariel.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson walked up to his stepmother and kissed her cheeks as he hugged her tightly.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“This is going to be a great celebration indeed but we also will have a very serious discussion at it and I am glad that my wisest friends will be in attendance to offer guidance.&amp;nbsp; My eldest son has chosen a lady whom he wishes to join with in the Holy Union.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;After the birth of Mirthan, the new council of Freeport restored the Shadowbane lands to Gilliadson and his family.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson had construction on the new estate started immediately.&amp;nbsp; The manor house was completed first and Gilliadson’s family moved in.&amp;nbsp; The next month Willanaome revealed herself to Gilliadson.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson was so overjoyed that Willa had been restored that he took her in as a member of the family.&amp;nbsp; The Shadowbane Estate was given the name Gil-Alani in honor of Gilliadson's birth parents at the suggestion of Lutiana.&amp;nbsp; Lutiana and Darthan grew to become Paladins of Marr and upstanding members of the knights of Truth.&amp;nbsp; Mirthan was enamored of the tales of his grandmother and those of Zephistophiles so he became a bard.&amp;nbsp; He and Shinu’s son, Ralnu, grew to be the best of friends and traveled together a lot.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson was recently made High Paladin of the Knights of Truth.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Shadowbane Homecoming is a yearly event that was started when the Shadowbane children started wandering Norrath seeking adventures and lives of their own.&amp;nbsp; It was six years ago that the rebuilding of the Shadowbane Estate, Gil-Alani, was completed and Lutiana started her quest for her Fiery Defender.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson made her promise to return home once each year on the anniversary date of her departure to share in a celebration.&amp;nbsp; The next year, Darthan started his quest and vowed to return for the celebration as well.&amp;nbsp; So was born the Shadowbane Homecoming celebration.&amp;nbsp; Two years later Mirthan started wandering Norrath with Ralnu and would return for the Homecoming celebration every year.&amp;nbsp; This year Obsecion decided to make this Homecoming celebration special by inviting Gilliadson’s cousins, old friends and his stepmother from Felwithe to attend.&amp;nbsp; Shinu, Whoos and their wives were sent invitations.&amp;nbsp; Obsecion knew that Gilliadson would send for Zephistophiles so she did not bother with his invitation.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson invited Zeph to attend every year.&amp;nbsp; The celebration date was yet four days away.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“I must go meet with this lady who wishes to join with my son.”&amp;nbsp; Said Obsecion and she walked out of the room.&amp;nbsp; Obsecion knocked on Vallea’s door.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Please come in.”&amp;nbsp; Came the call from the room.&amp;nbsp; Obsecion opened the door and walked into the room.&amp;nbsp; “Greetings Lady Shadowbane.&amp;nbsp; I am Vallea.”&amp;nbsp; Vallea said in perfect Elvish as she bowed to the Tunarean Knight.&amp;nbsp; Obsecion was surprised at first but did not let it show.&amp;nbsp; She quickly composed herself and addressed the young Drakkin.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“You greet me in my native tongue.&amp;nbsp; That is good.”&amp;nbsp; Said Obsecion in the draconic language.&amp;nbsp; “Has my son been teaching you?”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“He has taught me your language M’lady.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“He has taught you well.&amp;nbsp; So, you are the lady who wishes to join with my son.&amp;nbsp; I must say I never expected him to choose a mate from among the Children of Veeshan.&amp;nbsp; Getting my husband’s blessing upon this Union is not going to be an easy task but if the two of you manage to convince him then that is good enough for me.&amp;nbsp; The fact that you are here now says much.&amp;nbsp; There is much discussion going on all over Norrath concerning your people.&amp;nbsp; I attended a council session in Felwithe while I was there on the very subject.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“M’lady just as there are good and evil in most other races on Norrath there is also good and evil among my kind.&amp;nbsp; One difference though we have all bonded together toward the same goals.&amp;nbsp; While I may not personally condone the methods of Shadow Knights I have had to work with a few to help clear out our space in Crescent Reach and did so willingly for the greater good of our people.&amp;nbsp; Does it make me any less of a holy warrior?&amp;nbsp; I think not.&amp;nbsp; I still stand by my beliefs of defending those who need defending and stamping out the departed that refuse to depart.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“You make your case very eloquently but what I really want to know is this.&amp;nbsp; Do you love my son enough to do whatever is in his best interest regardless of how it affects you?&amp;nbsp; It has been my husband’s intention that Darthan would take over the estate following the birth of his first son and I will not allow that to change.&amp;nbsp; We have just restored the Shadowbane legacy and we will not see it falter again in our lifetime.&amp;nbsp; I am not asking you to break it off with my son right now but what I am asking is would you be willing to do so if he cannot receive his father’s blessing?&amp;nbsp; You do know that he will not enter into the Holy Union with you until he does.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“M’lady I would not join with your son in Holy Union without the blessing of both your husband and Keikolin.&amp;nbsp; My progenitor has told me that if Lord Shadowbane approves then so will he.&amp;nbsp; But before Lord Shadowbane makes his final decision he must meet with Keikolin as there are some issues that your Husband should be made aware of.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Have you told him this yet?”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“No M’lady, I am going to inform him at Homecoming.&amp;nbsp; I am not trying to be deceitful.&amp;nbsp; I just do not want anything to hinder his preparations for Homecoming.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Very well Lady Vallea, I will say nothing of this to him for now and give you the opportunity to tell him according to your plan.&amp;nbsp; For now let us be family.&amp;nbsp; Come meet my sisters Luminye and Silyene.&amp;nbsp; I have not yet told Gilliadson that they came with me.”&amp;nbsp; The two ladies spent the rest of the day with Luminye and Silyene.&amp;nbsp; &lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Tell me Beloved, what is your impression of Vallea?”&amp;nbsp; Asked Gilliadson as his wife lay in his arms that night.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“I like her.&amp;nbsp; I think she would make a fine wife.&amp;nbsp; But she does have more to tell you which I promised to let her reveal to you when she felt she should.&amp;nbsp; Do not confront her about this.&amp;nbsp; She is honorable and will tell you what you need to know when the time is right.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“I will trust your judgment in this my love.&amp;nbsp; Now let us put this day behind us.”&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson pulled Obsecion close to him and well some things are just too private to tell.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Chapter 3: More Reunions&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Whoos and Sanlacy arrived the next day.&amp;nbsp; While age is difficult to tell on Frogloks, Barbarians of Halas showed theirs like their Human cousins.&amp;nbsp; Sanlacy was till quite beautiful for her age though the sorrow of burying her mother, Jildarie, recently still showed in her face.&amp;nbsp; &lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Gilliadson embraced Sanlacy when she and Whoos arrived.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“My deepest condolences to you Sanlacy.&amp;nbsp; We all felt the loss of your mother’s passing.&amp;nbsp; If there is anything I or my house can do for you please do not hesitate to ask.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Thank you Gilliadson.”&amp;nbsp; Said Sanlacy.&amp;nbsp; “You have always been a true friend to us and there is no more that I can ask of you.&amp;nbsp; Time catches up to all of us sooner or later.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Shinu and his wife arrived the next day.&amp;nbsp; Shinu showed no outward signs of his age other than his fur not being as lustrous as it was in his youth.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Shinu, old friend!&amp;nbsp; Welcome to my home!&amp;nbsp; Apparently my wife has been busy.”&amp;nbsp; Said Gilliadson as he slapped the Vah Shir on the back.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Gilliadson!&amp;nbsp; I would not have missed this for the world!&amp;nbsp; I hear my son will be here as well.&amp;nbsp; Where is the kitchen?”&amp;nbsp; Shinu laughed.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Anything you need just ask one of the servants.&amp;nbsp; I am sure Obsecion has informed them of your appetite.&amp;nbsp; Do not tell Lutiana about your son coming.&amp;nbsp; Mirthan wants his arrival to be a surprise to her.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Ahh understood old friend.”&amp;nbsp; Shinu and his wife went into the manor to unpack.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Later that day, Darthan returned with Zephistophiles and Draigathar.&amp;nbsp; Zephistophiles’ once flame-red hair was now quite gray and his face was starting to tell the tale of years.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Zephistophiles!&amp;nbsp; How are things at the tavern?&amp;nbsp; Still spinning tales of our glory days for your customers?&amp;nbsp; Draigathar!&amp;nbsp; Welcome!&amp;nbsp; My home is yours as long as you are here.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Thank you Gilliadson.&amp;nbsp; The blessings of Quellious upon you and your house.”&amp;nbsp; Said Draigathar.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Gill!&amp;nbsp; Me old friend!&amp;nbsp; Though, ye don’t look near as old as I do now.&amp;nbsp; Those blessings o’ Tunare and Marr have been good ta ye.&amp;nbsp; If ye start adventurin’ again ye’ll have ta take me daughter along ta be yer chronicler.&amp;nbsp; I’m too old fer that now.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“I do not think there will be any more adventuring for me Zeph.&amp;nbsp; I have retired from wandering but that does not say that there are no more deeds for me to do.&amp;nbsp; Who knows what Marr will bring my way?&amp;nbsp; For now, Willa has prepared your room.&amp;nbsp; Please go in and make yourself at home.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Thank ye Gill.&amp;nbsp; We are looking forward to this celebration.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;The next day was the day before the Homecoming and Lutiana rose early that morning and stood at the gate.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Look at her.&amp;nbsp; You know she is going to be there until he arrives.&amp;nbsp; Maybe you should have told her.”&amp;nbsp; Said Obsecion as she was looking out the window at her daughter.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“I have never refused a reasonable request of any of our children.&amp;nbsp; I do not intend to start now.&amp;nbsp; He will be here today and her reaction will be well worth it all.”&amp;nbsp; Said Gilliadson as he stood behind his wife and pulled her in close to him.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson gently kissed Obsecion’s neck before releasing her.&amp;nbsp; “I will have Willa take her breakfast to her out there.&amp;nbsp; I know she will not come in for it.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;All that day more friends of Gilliadson and Obsecion arrived.&amp;nbsp; Azzor, whom Gilliadson served a tour of duty in Veksar with arrived early in the morning.&amp;nbsp; Leorah and Abeab arrived a little later.&amp;nbsp; Much to the joy of Willa, Snakepaw arrived with several kegs of ale.&amp;nbsp; The sun was going down when Lutiana saw two figures approaching from the West.&amp;nbsp; When they got close enough to be recognized, Lutiana’s heart leaped in her chest and she ran out to meet them.&amp;nbsp; Lutiana jumped into the arms of her little brother, who was not so little now.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson and Obsecion watched the scene from their bedroom window.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“See?&amp;nbsp; I told you it would be well worth it.”&amp;nbsp; Remarked Gilliadson.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Yes you did.”&amp;nbsp; Said Obsecion as she rubbed his shoulders.&amp;nbsp; “We shall let those two catch up and we will welcome our son home in the morning.&amp;nbsp; Now come to bed and remind me how much you love me.”&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
