      <title>The New Shadowbane  Part 2</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Roleplaying&amp;message.id=12464#M12464</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;P&gt;Chapter 4:&amp;nbsp; Crescent Reach&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Lord Gilliadson I am sorry I have not been able to bring this up to you before now and I was not aware of how big this celebration was going to be but we need to make a quick trip to Crescent Reach.&amp;nbsp; You must meet with Keikolin before you have any discussion and come to any decision regarding whether you will bless our Union.&amp;nbsp; I brought a few spells for Willanaome that she could use to transport us to Blightfire Moor.&amp;nbsp; From there, it is a run of an hour to Crescent Reach with bard assistance.“&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Well then we had better get moving.&amp;nbsp; Something that is this important I think I will want Zephistophiles, Willa and my wife along.&amp;nbsp; We should be back in plenty of time for the gathering tonight.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“I believe we will.&amp;nbsp; I can have Willa bind me here and we can have my brother port us all back.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Sounds like a plan to me.&amp;nbsp; I am sorry I did not give you the opportunity to bring this up before now.&amp;nbsp; Things have been quite busy here.”&amp;nbsp; The five of them gathered together and Vallea handed the scrolls to Willa who then copied them into her spell book.&amp;nbsp; Willa took a few moments to memorize a few spells and then started casting.&amp;nbsp; Vallea, Darthan and Zephistophiles were spirit bound in the manor.&amp;nbsp; Willa then cast the portal spell for Blightfire Moor.&amp;nbsp; The party appeared in the middle of a set of druid rings on a hill.&amp;nbsp; Before them was an ancient Treant.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Be careful out there.”&amp;nbsp; Warned the Treant.&amp;nbsp; “All of the other Treants out there have been corrupted and are rotting away.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Thank you for the warning.”&amp;nbsp; Said Willa.&amp;nbsp; Zephistophiles pulled out his drum and started beating a cadence on it.&amp;nbsp; The group’s legs were filled with energy and they started running toward Crescent Reach.&amp;nbsp; When they entered the city many Drakkin came and welcomed Darthan and Vallea back.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson was impressed with the reaction.&amp;nbsp; Many of them stared in awe at Gilliadson once they found out who he was.&amp;nbsp; Vallea led the group through the city and into the Grove where the six creators of the Drakkin were.&amp;nbsp; Vallea brought the group to the gold Dragon Keikolin, the bringer of enlightenment.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“So you are the great Gilliadson Shadowbane, the father of our friend Darthan.&amp;nbsp; Welcome to Crescent Reach.”&amp;nbsp; Said the great gold Dragon.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Greetings Lady Keikolin, Child of Veeshan.&amp;nbsp; I am sure you know why I am here.”&amp;nbsp; Said Gilliadson in the draconic tongue.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Yes and I am glad you came since there are a few things you will need to know about such a Union of our children.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“You have my attention.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“First, you must know that any children born of this Union will be Drakkin.&amp;nbsp; It is because of the Dragon blood.&amp;nbsp; No matter how many generations.&amp;nbsp; Second, the Drakkin partner of such Unions willfully determines the gender of each child born.&amp;nbsp; Lastly, all Drakkin are Children of Veeshan and will ultimately pay homage to her though they may honor any of the other gods of their choosing.&amp;nbsp; Vallea still holds the Marr twins in high regard.&amp;nbsp; I know your main concern is in preserving the Shadowbane bloodline and traditions and I can see where these conditions can ruin that.&amp;nbsp; However, our children are both honorable and they can be sworn to uphold your traditions as well as keeping the bloodlines of both Shadowbane and Veeshan intact.&amp;nbsp; Remember that these Drakkin were once wholly human and part of them still is.&amp;nbsp; Darthan you must realize that if this Union takes place then you will be the last fully Human Shadowbane in your line.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“I do understand that and if my father is willing to allow this then I do swear that my eldest son will also become a Knight of Truth as well as a paladin of the Wings of Virtue and I will teach him to continue this legacy.”&amp;nbsp; Said Darthan&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Also be mindful that once the Dragon blood awakens in your children they must come here to begin their training and receive the gift of breath from me before they can begin any other training.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson Shadowbane word of your deeds and your honor has even reached the ears of the Circle here.&amp;nbsp; I myself would not see such a legacy end.&amp;nbsp; I will do all in my power to ensure that it continues for as long as I draw breath.”&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson pondered these things for a few minutes before speaking.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“I accept your offers and your oaths and unless my friends have any arguments to persuade me otherwise, I will give my blessing upon this Union.&amp;nbsp; My son you do know that according to our oldest tradition when you bear your first son, Gil-Alani will be yours.&amp;nbsp; You are to carry on that tradition with your eldest son.&amp;nbsp; You must make sure that he joins the ranks of the Knights of Truth by at least performing the tests for his testimony as you and I have.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Father I will do as you have commanded.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Where is this Union to take place?&amp;nbsp; Have the two of you decided?”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“We would be honored if Lady Keikolin would officiate the Union for us along with the High Priest of Marr.&amp;nbsp; I would also institute this as a tradition for all Shadowbanes of my line from here on.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Darthan I would be most pleased to perform this service.&amp;nbsp; My Daughter, is all of this agreeable to you as well?”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Yes Mother it is.”&amp;nbsp; Replied Vallea.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Well then it all seems in order.&amp;nbsp; We have a Homecoming to get back to where I will make the announcement and will officially give my blessing.&amp;nbsp; Vallea would you fetch your brother so he can return us home?&amp;nbsp; Udra Lady Keikolin.&amp;nbsp; I look forward to seeing you again.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Udra Lord Shadowbane.”&amp;nbsp; Said Keikolin&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“As you wish, Lord Shadowbane.”&amp;nbsp; Said Vallea and she went to her brother and brought him to the group.&amp;nbsp; Vinlo cast his portal spell and the five were back in Gil-Alani.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Chapter 5:&amp;nbsp; The Celebration&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Everyone was gathered in the main hall, ready for the festivities to begin.&amp;nbsp; The Shadowbane family stood outside the door preparing to enter.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Vallea I would wish you to wait out here until I make the announcement.”&amp;nbsp; Said Gilliadson.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“As you wish M’lord.”&amp;nbsp; Agreed Vallea&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“And you can address me as father if you like.&amp;nbsp; You are not one of my servants.&amp;nbsp; You are a member of my family or at least soon will be.”&amp;nbsp; Vallea smiled and hugged the great knight.&amp;nbsp; The Shadowbanes entered the room and all the guests stood to their feet.&amp;nbsp; “Please, all of you, be seated.”&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson paused while the guests reseated themselves around the huge banquet table.&amp;nbsp; The Shadowbanes moved to their seats.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson was at the head of the table, Obsecion on his right, Lutiana and then Mirthan seated next to her.&amp;nbsp; On his left were Darthan, and empty chair and then Willanaome.&amp;nbsp; Willa served as the Head Servant of the Shadowbane house of her own volition in all other respects she was treated as a member of the family.&amp;nbsp; This was the largest gathering of friends and family of Shadowbane that had ever taken place.&amp;nbsp; Obsecion had sent out invitations to all of those who had journeyed with them that were still alive.&amp;nbsp; There were members of the old Fellowship of the Unbroken Adventurers guild, which Gilliadson had led for a season, as well as many friends from the Legends of Madcap Guild, which had taken in the surviving members of Fellowship when it disbanded.&amp;nbsp; Many allies of Legends attended as well, Pohaku and Haertagold and Hullk, the Ogre Warrior who had joined Gilliadson on a few campaigns to name a few.&amp;nbsp; All of the Knights of Truth were in the Hall as well.&amp;nbsp; The Shadowbanes were seated except for Gilliadson and Obsecion.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson addressed the gathering.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Welcome all of you to the fifth annual Shadowbane Homecoming.&amp;nbsp; Normally this event consists of just a few close friends and family but I see that my Beloved had made other plans without my knowing.”&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson turned to Obsecion and kissed her.&amp;nbsp; “Thank you my love.”&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson turned back to the assembly.&amp;nbsp; “I think it is only fitting that we begin this celebration with a period of silence in honor of those of our friends and loved ones who have departed our world.”&amp;nbsp; Everyone went silent for a few moments.&amp;nbsp; “Now I have an announcement to make before we begin the feast.&amp;nbsp; My Son Darthan has finally chosen one whom he wishes to join in the Holy Union with and she has met the approval of both his mother and me.”&amp;nbsp; Darthan stood up went to the door and opened it.&amp;nbsp; “It brings me great pleasure to present to you Vallea of Crescent Reach.”&amp;nbsp; Vallea walked into the room, took Darthan’s arm and was escorted to her seat.&amp;nbsp; The room was silent.&amp;nbsp; Vallea addressed Gilliadson.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“It brings me great honor to become a member of this prestigious family.&amp;nbsp; I do have something that must be done yet before we can go any further.&amp;nbsp; Lord Shadowbane, High Paladin of the Knights of Truth, I have a quest that I had started before my awakening but I was unable to continue it until now.&amp;nbsp; Since you are following old traditions as well as starting some new ones, I feel it is only fitting that I should carry one on that started with you and Lady Shadowbane.”&amp;nbsp; Vallea pulled a small token out of her pocket and handed it to Gilliadson.&amp;nbsp; “I think you recognize this.&amp;nbsp; I had received it but I awakened before I was to turn it in to your predecessor.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“A token of Truth.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“It seems fitting that a son of the greatest of the Knights of Truth should marry one also.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“So it shall be done!”&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson sent one of the squires for his sword.&amp;nbsp; “I have no testimony here to present to you.”&amp;nbsp; A quill, ink and parchment were brought to Gilliadson and he quickly scribed the words of the Testimony of Truth to the new parchment.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson handed the quill to Vallea, who then signed it after reading it.&amp;nbsp; The squire returned, knelt before Gilliadson and handed him the sword.&amp;nbsp; “It is always an honor and a pleasure to welcome a new squire as a full member of the Knights of Truth and this time is even more so.&amp;nbsp; Vallea are you prepared to take your oath?”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“I am.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Kneel before me Vallea.”&amp;nbsp; Commanded Gilliadson.&amp;nbsp; Vallea complied and Gilliadson drew his Fiery Defender from its scabbard its flames dancing along the length of the blade.&amp;nbsp; As Gilliadson touched each of her shoulders, Vallea could feel the warmth of the blade.&amp;nbsp; It was pleasantly warm instead of the searing burn that the enemies of Shadowbane usually feel as the blade passes through their flesh.&amp;nbsp; “The only words that come to my mind to speak now are the very words spoken at my knighting many years ago.&amp;nbsp; To be a Knight of Truth in itself is a great honor and carries with it great responsibility to carry forward the ideals of the Truthbringer.&amp;nbsp; A Knight of Truth must be a man or woman of great integrity.&amp;nbsp; This evening we welcome one such lady to our ranks.&amp;nbsp; It is by the authority of Mithaniel Marr that I hereby welcome you to the ranks of the Knights of Truth with all rights, privileges and responsibilities thereof.&amp;nbsp; Arise Lady Vallea of Crescent Reach.”&amp;nbsp; Vallea stood and read the Testimony of Truth aloud to those gathered.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“I believe in the might of Mithaniel Marr.&amp;nbsp; I shall uphold the words of Marr and defend them with my life.&amp;nbsp; I shall protect the righteous weak and avenge the souls of those whose life has been taken for naught.&amp;nbsp; From this day forth I shall become a living vessel for the ideals of the Truthbringer and if I should ever falter from his grace may he cast me from this life and into the lifeless void.&amp;nbsp; Praise be to Marr!”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“PRAISE BE TO MARR!!”&amp;nbsp; Echoed the rest of the attendees.&amp;nbsp; Vallea took her seat beside Darthan and held his hand.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson then continued his address.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Six years ago my daughter, Lutiana, began her travels in the world.&amp;nbsp; It was then that I made her promise to return home on this date every year.&amp;nbsp; The following year Darthan began his journeys and promised to return on this date.&amp;nbsp; Thus was instituted Shadowbane Homecoming.&amp;nbsp; Every year since then, we have gathered with a few friends on this date and shared tales of our travels.&amp;nbsp; Mirthan started his travels two years later.&amp;nbsp; This year as I stated earlier it seems that my wife decided to make this one special for some reason.&amp;nbsp; And, with a little unknown assistance from my son, it is special.&amp;nbsp; I hereby bestow my blessing upon the upcoming Union of Darthan and Vallea and welcome a new member to the house of Shadowbane.&amp;nbsp; Norrath is an ever-changing world and in order for us to survive in it we must also adapt to the changes.”&amp;nbsp; Darthan put his arm around Vallea and pulled her close to his side as Gilliadson concluded his speech,&amp;nbsp; “Behold the future of Shadowbane!”&amp;nbsp; Said Gilliadson as he swept his arm toward his son and Vallea.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;The room burst into a round of applause as everyone rose to their feet.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson raised his mug in a toast.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Here is to Darthan and Vallea.&amp;nbsp; May you both continue in the grace of Mithaniel Marr!&amp;nbsp; May you live long, live well and live with passion.&amp;nbsp; May you both bring honor to Marr, Veeshan and the name of Shadowbane.&amp;nbsp; Finally, may your children bring you the joys that all of my children have.”&amp;nbsp; All the guests raised their mugs and joined in the toast.&amp;nbsp; “This is the finest Tuneweaver Ale I have ever tasted.&amp;nbsp; Zephistophiles you have outdone yourself this time.”&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;“Twas not I who made the ale Gill.&amp;nbsp; Twas me son.”&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson and Zephistophiles laughed together.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;The Celebration lasted all through the night and into the next day as the Shadowbane children shared their tales with the assembled guests.&amp;nbsp; No one left the celebration hungry, not even Shinu.&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Epilogue:&lt;BR&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;BR&gt;Darthan and Vallea were joined several months later in one of the grandest ceremonies to ever take place in the history of the Shadowbane family.&amp;nbsp; Vallea gave birth to their first son two years later.&amp;nbsp; They named him Barathir.&amp;nbsp; Shortly afterward Darthan and his family moved into Gil-Alani and Gilliadson and Obsecion moved into an apartment in Freeport.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson continued as High Paladin for three more years before retiring and moving back to his old cottage in Kelethin.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson and Obsecion lived for many years after and witnessed the birthing of several generations of Drakkin Shadowbane.&amp;nbsp; Gilliadson and Obsecion died together and were buried in the family crypt next to Gilliad and Alani’s remains.&amp;nbsp; The Shadowbane traditions are carried on to this day.&amp;nbsp; I am Daletar Tuneweaver, a direct descendant of the great lore master and bard Zephistophiles Tuneweaver and the last of the Shadowbane chroniclers.&lt;BR&gt;&lt;/P&gt;</description>
