      <title>A lil EQ Story, Enjoy</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Roleplaying&amp;message.id=12455#M12455</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;There I was staring at the beautiful tree's of the city of kelethin, the moon flickered through the swaying branches of the tree's. It was a new beginning. I found myself lost in this mysterious world of norrath. I maneuvered my way through all the elven merchants selling various trinkets and general goods. Often I would ask for directions to the nearest training area, however everyone was too busy to point me in the right direction. As I walking I managed to take a wrong turn.... I nearly fell to my death..... I was dangling from the top of a lift... Someone hit the lift button and I managed to climb onto the platform to saftey. It was then that I knew that nearly falling to my death was just a preminition of things to come. I could go on all day about how keen and agile the wasps are.... but that would probably only lead to the many stories of me experiencing the afterlife in small sessions as I ran back to my corpse.&lt;p&gt;Many full moons later I found myself stumbling across a forbidden keep. I managed to work my way right into the heart of the threat my fellow kelethinians worst fear. The orcs, perticularly Keep crushbone. I cut through the orcs fast, it was almost as if I was chopping my way through a thick jungle...I charged my way to the top of the keep, and cut down their chieftain....finally a notch in my belt to kick off a neverending career of slaying evil......Crushbone was only the beginning...&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I managed to spend a few nights at an inn in kelethin, recoverying from the wounds I sustained fighting the chieftain, and his sidekick... I knew the my next mission was to cleanse a dungeon off the caldron, a place called unrest.... As a small boy my father would tell me stories about such an evil place, that it was at one time a flourishing community wealthy highelfs... however a great curse was bestowed upon them, and as they died they were left forever haunting the mansion. In perticular was a ghost dwarf, who dwells in the bowells of the ancient construction. It was there, that I found that i didn't quite plan for the long haul. I didn't plan on staying too many nights in the forbidden zone, however I found myself low on rations and water.. I was becoming weak.... I'd never give up, but out of desperation I foraged the area, unfortunately I wasn't able to scrounge enough to keep myself full enuogh to fight the evil minons of unrest.... It was when I met this mysterious creature... It was a pure white wolf, almost as if the gods themself had blessed this beautiful creature, and sent it to norrath to watch over those in need.... Although this creature was clearly a wolf, it spoke to me.....the wolf's voice was a very comforting woman voice "hello, are you okay?" I said, yes, do you have any food? I felt strange asking a wolf, but I figured a talking wolf was strange enough, It's not more stranger asking her for food.... the wolf slowly transformed into a beautiful elven girl... I was pretty much stunned---from the moment I layed eyes on her angelic face I was mezmerized..... I was drawn to her, because I knew nothing of her, or her kind.... After she summoned me food out of thin air! She disappeared, as if she never existed, however I was full so clearly I wasn't hallucinating..I kept fighting in unrest until the undead were supressed enough to leave Butch block alone for a few months...I fought in lesser faydark, and all over butcherblock, I traveled to the oasis and helped get rid of their crocodile problem.....Eventually I found my way to a place called high hold keep.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It was in highhold keep that I found myself struggling for experience at my 22nd season. I was battling a goblin, when I heard that angelic voice, I felt the surge of light coarse through me as my body bathed in blue lights. I turned around and my mystery woman was in her wolf form. We decided to team up officially to slay the goblins that plagued hhk. I found out she had someone in her life, that didn't bother me, I just enjoyed being around her, and talking about anything that was on her mind. I later met her someone of 6 years. He was a very nice person, however he was a peck..... and she was an elf, I've seen stranger things, but I kept an open mind and dismissed the fact that he was a PECK...The months went by, and our friendship grew stronger... Vuluxy was having problems with her friend, and I tried to be there to console her... My love for this druid only grew stronger by the day....I would go to sleep thinking about Lady Vuluxy, and in the morning I couldn't wait to get purple text of a message from her. At that time in my life, this wonderful elf completed me.. She kept me sane, and focused. Whenever I thought about flying off the handle, or saying something stupid I thought about her, and how it would affect her..I tried to never rock the boat when we would group with other ppl, however sometimes I'd get a little jealous, or angry if someone said something to insult her or our PDA. I was young, and inexperienced with love, but that doesn't mean I didn't have a strong emotional tie to this woman. Many seasons later, Vuluxy and I decided to take our relationship to a different level.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We left the ethereal world and decided to connect on a completely different level. We met on the material plane. It took her about 4 hours to travel to my village in the material world. From the moment I saw her, I walked over to her and gave her this huge hug, I couldn't let go of her... Everything was so perfect, she was on a long journey, she smelled like she had just ran 20 miles, and I couldn't let her go, I loved everything about her, her smile... her smell, the look on her face when she first layed eyes on me. We got back to my ride and I couldn't let go of her, or keep my eyes off her, we kissed slowly, and then..... we kept kissing, this went on for about 4 hours. I couldn't love her anymore than I did at that moment. I was at peace, I would truely more comfortable than I had ever been.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;We rode back to my place, and we slept with each other under the stars... it was rather cold out, but she put her leg over mine, and held me tight, we were definately warm enough.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The next day I took her sledding at "Suicide hill". we played in the snow.... and had a great time. It was that night that we first made love, and every night after that we made love some more. We had a beautiful christmas... and then it was time to say goodbye. This was particularly difficult for me because everything was perfect. I didn't want any of it to end, the sad state of reality was setting in, and of course the question was, will I see her again soon?&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;1 week later, she flew back to my village..and we spent more nights together, enjoying each others company, and making love....life was definately surreal.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It finally came to the end of her visit where we had to say goodbye again. For some reason this was more difficult than saying goodbye the first time...&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I was young, I had no real direction, but I had a plan. I was going to join the Airborne infantry. I spent 14 weeks training, 4 weeks in hold over, and 3 weeks in airborne school.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Every week of my 14 week basic training, I would get 1 or 2 letters from my dear "Vuluxy". After I got moved to hold over for airborne school, I called to give her my new address. Unfortunately every time i had a chance to call, which was once a week nobody answered... It was a month later I found that she changed her number. She said it was because her old boyfriend was hounding her. We talked about life plans together, and I Tried to call her every week. All throughout airborne school she never answered her phone.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I took hometown recruiting for 2 weeks plus 2 weeks leave at home. I called her, but never could get in touch with her..&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;It was when I was stationed at Fort Bragg, and I was getting settled into my unit with the 82nd airborne division, I got a call from her. We talked, and it seemed like we were more friends than anything else. I asked her if I could come see her that weekend, and she said no she was going out with her friends. This was likes a stab in the heart I just went through over 20 weeks of training, and she didn't want to take the time to see me that weekend, something was wrong..... I dismissed the negative notions I had..... I asked her when would be a good time to come see her? She said, "how about next weekend? Call me friday!" I was pretty excited..... although also very cautious. I didn't want to build falsehope, just to be buried in the ground..... That following week I called, nobody answered. I checked my email.... it said:&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Dear "soandso"&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;The basic breakdown and key points are "your too young for me" "your inexperienced" "We learned a lot from each other" "But I'm not ready for a commitment right now".&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Pretty much that was information entailed in the Dear "Soandso" letter of, I just stomped your heart out.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;Truth of the matter is If your living in pure bliss, grab that bliss by the reins and milk it for all it's worth, happiness is priceless, however coming off of happiness will leave you in the worst down period you've ever been in. It's like being forced to quit cold turkey, except you didn't have a choice.....&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;simply put, the definition of love could be that it's an addicting drug with the potential of heart breaking side effects.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;And that if you venture outside the ethereal world, you risk getting hurt, but if you never take that leap, you won't experience true happiness even if it's temporary.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;I hope you guys enjoyed the story,I'm sure it's one of many stories that have similar characteristics. This particular case happened 5 years ago, and in the realm of the Tribunal. Also, the reason I posted it because for some reason I wanted to do some creative writing! If the lore is incorrect, or I don't use all the right tenses, please get over it =p&lt;/p&gt;</description>
