    <item>
      <title>Rawlodan and Rhodace</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Roleplaying&amp;message.id=12454#M12454</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Rawlodan the Barbarian Shaman and Rhodace the Human Paladin, having made their way to the slave revolt camp in Gloomingdeep at the same time, decided that things would go a lot easier helping the revolt if they teamed up. After aquiring the Kobold Skull Charm from Arias they set out to make a contribution to the revolt effort.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;After doing several tasks which involved helping to clear some of the vermin from around the camp area and killing several rather nasty spiders, they learned that they could obtain some valuable items by ransacking the numerous barrels which the slow witted kobolds seem to have left around the caves. In no time at all Rhodace found herself well equipped with a bow, quiver and several arrows.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;They then accepted the task of sabotaging the kobold supplies down by the fort from Zajeer. Fighting their way towards the fort, they easily dispatched several grunts and warriors, gaining confidence and loot along the way. As they entered the final tunnel to the fort, they encountered a kobold captain and, unfortunately were not of sufficient strength to dispatch this fiend. They both soon found themselves back at the soulbinder in the rebel camp.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;At that point it was decided that they would rest and fight again on another day.&lt;/DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;</description>
